			<ns0:name>noelal...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/113000403807150741221/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We instantiate a nacl app object which is needed for various tracking
reasons.  However, the object is constructed and pointed to locally in
&amp;quot;main&amp;quot;, so it is not globally visible, yet several modules need the object
to function correctly.  This has lead to us having several copies of the NAP in several modules, such as signalling and debugging.

We need to either decide that we will not support multiple NAPs in one process and thus just make it global, or we should provide a mechanism for getting the current NAP, for asynchronously triggered events such as signals or debugging.




&lt;b&gt;Please provide any additional information below and attach any relevant&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;source files.&lt;/b&gt;
